  "prompt": "Does Toptal ever do any discounts?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge up to October 2023, Toptal primarily operates on a premium pricing model that reflects its focus on connecting clients with top-tier freelancers and professionals across various fields, including software development, design, finance, and project management. Because of this high-quality, vetted talent pool, Toptal doesn't commonly offer standard discounts in the way some other service providers might.\n\nHowever, there are a few scenarios where discounts or special pricing might be available:\n\n1. **Trial Periods or Pilot Projects:** Toptal sometimes offers trial periods or pilot projects at a reduced rate, allowing clients to assess the fit before committing to longer-term engagements.\n\n2. **Long-Term Contracts:** Committing to longer-term projects or contracts might provide some leverage for negotiating better rates.\n\n3. **Referral Programs:** Toptal has, in the past, implemented referral programs where existing clients or freelancers can refer new clients and receive discounts or other benefits in return.\n\n4. **Special Promotions:** During certain times of the year or for specific events, Toptal might run special promotions or discounts. These are typically announced through their official channels.\n\n5. **Non-Profit or Educational Discounts:** In some cases, organizations like non-profits or educational institutions might be eligible for special pricing, though this would likely require direct negotiation with Toptal's sales team.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information regarding discounts or special pricing, it's best to contact Toptal directly through their [official website](https://www.toptal.com/contact) or reach out to their sales team. They can provide details tailored to your specific needs and circumstances.",
